#fff;background-color:#90b78d;border-color:#90b78d;border-radius:3px;padding:5px 8px" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-jump-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewbox="0 0 24 24"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" fill="#ffffff"><path data-color="color-2" d="M9,2h6c0.6,0,1-0.4,1-1s-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,0,8,0.4,8,1S8.4,2,9,2z"></path> <path fill="#ffffff" d="M16,11V5c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1H9C8.4,4,8,4.4,8,5v6H1.9L12,23.6L22.1,11H16z"></path></g></svg></span> Jump to Recipe</a> <a href="https://www.homeandplate.com/wprm_print/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe" style="color:#fff;background-color:#90b78d;border-color:#90b78d;border-radius:3px;padding:5px 8px" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-print-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent" data-recipe-id="10413" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg width="16px" height="16px" viewbox="0 0 24 24" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g fill="#ffffff"><g><path d="M17.5454,0.0005 C18.2904,0.0005 18.9004,0.6105 18.9004,1.3565 L18.9004,1.3565 L18.9004,4.9445 L21.9904,4.9445 C23.0954,4.9445 24.0004,5.8485 24.0004,6.9535 L24.0004,6.9535 L24.0004,17.2415 C24.0004,18.3465 23.0954,19.2505 21.9904,19.2505 L21.9904,19.2505 L19.8414,19.2505 L19.8414,22.2795 C19.8414,23.1725 19.1104,23.9035 18.2174,23.9035 L18.2174,23.9035 L5.7834,23.9035 C4.8894,23.9035 4.1594,23.1725 4.1594,22.2795 L4.1594,22.2795 L4.1594,19.2505 L2.0104,19.2505 C0.9044,19.2505 0.0004,18.3465 0.0004,17.2415 L0.0004,17.2415 L0.0004,6.9535 C0.0004,5.8485 0.9044,4.9445 2.0104,4.9445 L2.0104,4.9445 L5.0984,4.9445 L5.0984,1.3565 C5.0984,0.6105 5.7094,0.0005 6.4554,0.0005 L6.4554,0.0005 Z M17.8414,15.5975 L6.1594,15.5975 L6.1594,21.9035 L17.8414,21.9035 L17.8414,15.5975 Z M21.9904,6.9445 L2.0104,6.9445 L2.0004,17.2415 L4.1594,17.2425 L4.1594,15.2215 C4.1594,14.3285 4.8894,13.5975 5.7834,13.5975 L5.7834,13.5975 L18.2174,13.5975 C19.1104,13.5975 19.8414,14.3285 19.8414,15.2215 L19.8414,15.2215 L19.8414,17.2495 L21.9904,17.2505 L22.0004,6.9535 L21.9904,6.9445 Z M6.1632,9.1318 C6.7902,9.1318 7.2992,9.6408 7.2992,10.2678 C7.2992,10.8948 6.7902,11.4028 6.1632,11.4028 L6.1632,11.4028 L5.0992,11.4028 C4.4722,11.4028 3.9632,10.8948 3.9632,10.2678 C3.9632,9.6408 4.4722,9.1318 5.0992,9.1318 L5.0992,9.1318 Z M16.6304,2.2715 L7.3704,2.2715 L7.3704,4.6845 L16.6304,4.6845 L16.6304,2.2715 Z"></path></g></g></g></svg></span> Print Recipe</a> </div> <p><em>This is the perfect sugar cookie recipe for all your holiday baking. These sugar cookies are soft yet chewy and keep their shape while baking.&nbsp;</em></p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="739" height="1024" alt="Plate of sugar cookies covered in red and green sprinkles on a white plate" sizes="(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookies-recipe-1-739x1024.jpg 739w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookies-recipe-1-216x300.jpg 216w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookies-recipe-1-768x1065.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookies-recipe-1.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookies-recipe-1-739x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10409 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTE2MTo3NjQ=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTE2MTo3NjQ=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzM5IDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI3MzkiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>Perfect for the holidays or any time of year, these cookies require only 6 ingredients, no chilling of the dough and about eight minutes in the oven.&nbsp; </p> <p>They can be rolled into balls, or rolled out flat and cut into shapes using cookie cutters.</p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="683" height="1024" alt="Plate of frosted sugar cookies with sprinkles" sizes="(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-6-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-6-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-6.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-6-683x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10403 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTE4MTo3MzA=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTE4MTo3MzA=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjgzIDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI2ODMiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">Ingredients in Sugar Cookies</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>Your shopping list will include: </p> <p><strong>Butter</strong>: allow the butter to soften at room temperature for several hours. The key to this recipe is soft, soft butter.</p> <p><strong>Sugar</strong>: this recipe calls for granulated sugar. I always have a bag ready for use in my pantry.</p> <p><strong>Vanilla extract</strong>: pure vanilla extract is needed for this recipe. Not the imitation stuff. Yes it can be expensive but it adds a wonderful flavor to the cookies.</p> <p><strong>Egg</strong>: pick up a carton of large eggs. While you will only need one most baking recipes call for eggs so they won’t go to waste.</p> <p><strong>Flour</strong>: A bag of all purpose flour will do for this recipe.</p> <p><strong>Baking powder</strong>: pick up a fresh container of baking powder. If you can’t remember when you purchased your last container, toss it and buy fresh. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="683" height="1024" alt="Plate of frosted sugar cookies with unfrosted cookies in the background" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-1-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-1-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-1.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-1-683x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10398 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTIyOTo3Nzc=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTIyOTo3Nzc=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjgzIDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI2ODMiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Make Perfect Sugar Cookie Recipe</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>These cookies are the perfect balance of chewy and crispy and they are delicious plain or frosted. </p> <p>First allow the butter to soften to room temperature. This is an important step so the cookies have the right consistency and texture. </p> <p>I use a stand mixer but a hand mixer will work as well. Use a large bowl to blend the softened butter and sugar for about three minutes. Next, add the egg and vanilla and mix until just combined. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="768" height="1024" alt="Mixing stand with sugar cookie dough in the bowl" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-5-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-5-225x300.jpg 225w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-5.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-5-768x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10402 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTI2MTo2NDk=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTI2MTo2NDk=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzY4IDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI3NjgiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>Add the flour 1 cup at a time slowly so that it doesn’t fly all over the kitchen. Gradually add in the next 2 cups of flour before increasing the speed of your mixer.</p> <p>The dough will be the consistency of play dough – soft and moldable. </p> <p>Roll the dough into balls or roll out flat and use cookie cutters to create shapes before placing on a silicone or parchment lined baking sheet. </p> <p>Bake in a 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes depending on your oven. Eight minutes was the magic number in my oven. </p> <p>Remove the cookies from the oven and allow them to cool for five minutes before transferring them to a cooling rack. Allow the cookies to cool completely before frosting and decorating.</p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="768" height="1024" alt="Hand holding glass over a cookie ball on a cookie sheet" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-4-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-4-225x300.jpg 225w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-4.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-4-768x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10401 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTI5Mzo2NTY=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTI5Mzo2NTY=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzY4IDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI3NjgiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Form Sugar Cookie Dough</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>What I love about this easy cookie dough is that it can be scooped and rolled in your hands into smooth balls and baked, or rolled in your hands, placed on a baking sheet and gently pressed with a bottom of a glass. </p> <p>If you wanted to use cookie cutters, this dough can be rolled out flat to a quarter-inch thick using a rolling pin and pressed into desired shapes. </p> <p>When making holiday cookies with kids, I find using the glass method works best. If I want to get a bit creative and methodical, I’ll roll out this dough and use cookie cutters. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="768" height="1024" alt="Baking sheet of cookies ready for the oven" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-3-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-3-225x300.jpg 225w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-3.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-3-768x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10400 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTMyNTo2NDM=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTMyNTo2NDM=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzY4IDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI3NjgiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>My kids are artistic, but they are certainly not professional bakers or decorators and they get a little sloppy with the frosting. </p> <p>Spending time in the kitchen with your children is a great way to bond and celebrate the holidays.&nbsp;</p> <p>I don’t have all day to spend making cookies which is why this recipe works. Rolling out the dough takes&nbsp; time. Flattening balls of dough with the bottom of a glass is a time saver. </p> <p>All kids are proud of their cookie decorating skills, and these ideas below are easy for even the most creative and artistic kids. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="683" height="1024" alt="Collage of four types of decorative cookies: overhead shot of decorative cookies on a cookie sheet, a snowman cookie, Christmas tree cookies , and reindeer cookie." sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-8-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-8-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-8-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-8.jpg 1000w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-8-683x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10405 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTM1Mzo4NzA=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTM1Mzo4NzA=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjgzIDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI2ODMiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">What decorating ideas are easy for kids </h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p><strong>Reindeer</strong>: use pretzels for the antlers, a red candy for a Rudolph nose and edible candy eyes. </p> <p><strong>Melted snowman</strong>: mini chocolate chips for the eyes, a Rollo candy for Frosty’s hat and orange sprinkles for the carrot nose. </p> <p><strong>Christmas trees</strong>: green gel or frosting piping to make a tree and sprinkles, nonpareils and stars for the ornaments.&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Christmas lights</strong>: colored gel for the cord and M&Ms for the colored lights.&nbsp;<br /></p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">Can I Freeze Sugar Cookies</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>Yes the dough can be rolled into balls and frozen individually. Place the balls on a cookie sheet and place it in the freezer until frozen. Store the frozen balls in a zip lock bag until ready to use. These baked cookies also freeze well. Just make sure they’re cooled completely and not frosted before they go in the freezer. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="683" height="1024" alt="Closeup of fronsted sugar cookie" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2.jpg 800w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-683x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-10399 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTQwNTo3Mzg=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTQwNTo3Mzg=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNjgzIDEwMjQiIHdpZHRoPSI2ODMiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></figure> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Store the Perfect Sugar Cookie</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p>Allow the decorated cookies to sit for about an hour before storing. The frosting will be dry to the touch and will hold its shape when packaged in a sealed tight plastic container. </p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <h2 class="wp-block-heading">More Christmas Sweets</h2> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <ul class="wp-block-list"> <li><strong><a href="https://www.homeandplate.com/blog/white-chocolate-cranberry-pistachio-cookies/">White Chocolate Cranberry Pistachio Cookies</a></strong></li> <li><strong><a href="https://www.homeandplate.com/blog/pecan-butterball-cookies/">Pecan Butterball Cookies – Perfect for the holidays!</a></strong></li> <li><strong><a href="https://www.homeandplate.com/blog/3-ingredient-chocolate-peanut-butter-fudge/">Chocolate Peanut Butter Fudge – Just 3 Ingredients Needed!</a></strong></li> <li><strong><a href="https://www.homeandplate.com/blog/granola-blondie-bars-perfect-for-holiday-baking/">Granola Blondie Bars: perfect for holiday baking!</a></strong></li> </ul> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <p class="has-text-align-center"><strong>If you love this recipe, please leave a comment with a five-star rating. Be sure to follow HOME & PLATE on <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.facebook.com/homeandplate/" target="_blank">FACEBOOK</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.instagram.com/homeandplate/" target="_blank">INSTAGRAM</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.pinterest.com/homeandplate/" target="_blank">PINTEREST</a>&nbsp;for all the latest content, recipes and updates.</strong></p> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <div style="height:50px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div> <div id="recipe"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-container-10413" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="10413" data-servings="2"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-recipes"><div class="wprm-container-float-right"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-rounded"><img style="border-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-color:#666;border-radius:3px" width="167" height="250" alt="Closeup of fronsted sugar cookie" sizes="auto, (max-width: 167px) 100vw, 167px" nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2.jpg 800w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-200x300.jpg 200w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2-683x1024.jpg 683w" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/images/optimized/rev-ed5d556/www.homeandplate.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/perfect-sugar-cookie-recipe-2.jpg" class="attachment-250x250 size-250x250 nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTQ3Mzo4NTE=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTQ3Mzo4NTE=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDEyMDAiIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTIwMCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></div> </div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name wprm-block-text-bold">Perfect Sugar Cookie Recipe</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span class="wprm-recipe-author-with-image"><span class="wprm-recipe-author-image"><img style="border-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-color:#666;border-radius:50%" alt='' height='30' width='30' nitro-lazy-srcset="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/desktop/optimized/rev-ed5d556/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1dc61884508515d5b8bb6c0b7f2dc5fc.60cb72da9b662f59813f50cb8d7ff4b51ffe6eaba8febffdc716009224369a47 2x" nitro-lazy-src="https://cdn-ilegjii.nitrocdn.com/bPcaZsOEGZoEcYkQXaTqQAgFcDxAlLBQ/assets/desktop/optimized/rev-ed5d556/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e671d887af3dcc810ed8264c18faf3df.60cb72da9b662f59813f50cb8d7ff4b51ffe6eaba8febffdc716009224369a47" class="avatar avatar-30 photo nitro-lazy" decoding="async" nitro-lazy-empty id="MTQ3Nzo0ODU=-1" data-nitro-empty-id="MTQ3Nzo0ODU=-1" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAgMzAiIHdpZHRoPSIzMCIgaGVpZ2h0PSIzMCIgeG1sbnM9Imh0dHA6Ly93d3cudzMub3JnLzIwMDAvc3ZnIj48L3N2Zz4=" /></span><span class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author wprm-block-text-light">Ali Randall</span></span> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-summary wprm-block-text-normal"><span style="display:block">This is the perfect sugar cookie recipe for all your holiday baking. These sugar cookies are soft yet chewy and keep their shape while baking.&nbsp;</span></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="0" height="0" style="display:block;width:0px;height:0px"><defs><lineargradient id="wprm-recipe-rating-0-33"><stop offset="0%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="33%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="33%" stop-opacity="0"></stop><stop offset="100%" stop-opacity="0"></stop></lineargradient></defs><defs><lineargradient id="wprm-recipe-rating-0-50"><stop offset="0%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="50%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="50%" stop-opacity="0"></stop><stop offset="100%" stop-opacity="0"></stop></lineargradient></defs><defs><lineargradient id="wprm-recipe-rating-0-66"><stop offset="0%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="66%" stop-opacity="1"></stop><stop offset="66%" stop-opacity="0"></stop><stop offset="100%" stop-opacity="0"></stop></lineargradient></defs></svg><div id="wprm-recipe-rating-0" class="wprm-recipe-rating wprm-recipe-rating-recipe-10413 wprm-recipe-rating-inline"><span class="wprm-rating-star wprm-rating-star-1 wprm-rating-star-full" data-rating="1" data-color="#90b78d" style="font-size:1em"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewbox="0 0 24 24"><g transform="translate(0, 0)"><polygon fill="none" stroke="#90b78d" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-miterlimit="10" points="12,2.6 15,9 21.4,9 16.7,13.9 18.6,21.4 12,17.6 5.4,21.4 7.3,13.9 2.6,9 9,9 " stroke-linejoin="miter"></polygon></g></svg></span><span class="wprm-rating-star wprm-rating-star-2 wprm-rating-star-full" data-rating="2" data-color="#90b78d" style="font-size:1em"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewbox="0 0 24 24"><g transform="translate(0, 0)"><polygon fill="none" stroke="#90b78d" stroke-width="2" stroke-lineca